    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello!\r\nI've added a format for this type of sentences:\r\n```clojure\r\n:datetime-ago-format  \"{{number}} {{time-intervals}} {{ago}}\"\r\n```\r\nThis is the template for English locale, and translations will fall back to that by default. That corresponds to \"1 minute ago\" order.\r\n\r\nHowever, if there's a different order for some language, one can override this template, for example for German and Spanish:\r\n```clojure\r\n:datetime-ago-format  \"{{ago}} {{number}} {{time-intervals}}\"\r\n```\r\nThis corresponds to \"hace 1 minuto\", \"vor 1 Minute\". There are probably more languages like that, but I don't know those.",
